<h1>{{title}}</h1>
<!-- <blockquote class="note"><i><b>Update:</b> A new algorithm is being used which is much faster. Feel free to kick the tires and <a href="mailto:mkname@ajs.com">let me know</a> if you see anything different, better, worse or just interesting. There is also now <a href="http://www.3d6.net/aarons_essays/2008/10/updated-random-name-generator.html">a posting about this on my blog</a>, where you can leave a comment if you wish.</i></blockquote>-->

	<p class="intro">This random name generator can be used for roleplaying games,
	video games, or wherever you need a name for a fictional chracter.
	Each style of name below is generated by assembling
	word-parts from a list of names. This code was originally
	written to generate random words for
	<a href="http://www.ajs.com/ajswiki/Mkpasswd">mkpasswd</a>,
	a security tool. The names are chosen to
	represent a certain language or culture. For example for
	the American names, the 1990 US Census data was used,</p>
<table class="layout" border="0" width="100%"><tr width="100%"><td valign="top" width="20%">
<div class="sidebar"><h2>Specific Lists</h2>
<ul>
{% for lang in wordlists.languages %}
    <li> <a href="http://tools.ajs.com/mkname/{{lang.shortname}}">{{lang.longname}} ({{lang.count}})</a></li>
{% endfor %}
</div></td><td valign="top" width="80%">

{% for nameblock in nameblocks %}
    <div class="namelist" style="width: 31%;"><h2>{{nameblock.title}}</h2>
    <ul class="namelist"><pre class="namelist">
{% for name in nameblock.names %}{{name}}{% endfor %}
</pre></ul></div>

</td></tr></table>
<br class="sep" />
</ul>
